race.comment: BARBARY TALES (3) comes here following a seventh behind Surfingmakescents at Group Three level four weeks ago over 1720m at Melton. Ideally drawn and can take this out. THE BRIDE (7) settled handy then assumed control and dug deep to score in a 1720m race at Melton last start, arriving a nose ahead of her rivals to make it two wins from her past six runs. Tactics will be crucial from this wide draw. Tackles a similar assignment and she can make it two on the trot. SMILING MIA (1) is the next best after finishing runner-up over 2090m at Hobart last time out. ALWAYSATIGER (2) must be respected after scoring last start by a head at Burnie over 2180m.
